						               													<description>&amp;#10;             WINNER OF BEST WAR THEMED GAME IN THE 2021 52-card game contest ***&amp;#10;        &amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;OPERTION AKIMBO is the code name for a top secret Allied WWII mission to liberate key areas in northern France &amp;amp; set the stage for a full scale invasion at D-Day.  The game is a solo card game using a 2-sided 54 card deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You General, must organize the joint effort between the US, Canadian &amp;amp; English forces in this critical operation. Your task is to lay the optimal path through the French country side, organize men and air support &amp;amp; achieve key objectives. Finally, it is critical you deliver all 3 squads to the rendezvous point.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn you will choose 1 card &amp;amp; 1 side of that card to play. One side will be a path through the countryside with enemies to overcome &amp;amp; the other is a completed mission objective, unit forces to deploy, or air support.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You win by completing three 10 card paths, overcoming all enemies by either ground and air troops &amp;amp; completing 15 mission objectives before all cards are used.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is fully PnP on BGG and was designed for the 2021 54-Card deck contest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
